Double slits do not split light, but act as a geometric amplifier and sampler for diffused light fields. They screen valid diffusion routes and guide massive particles to complete overall path separation. Multiple stable optical channels with clear intervals are formed, and dark fringes naturally appear in path gaps without any wave interference.
